-- Britain May See Toll Instituted on Existing Road, Telegraph Says
-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 2012-07-18T23:22:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-18/britain-may-see-toll-instituted-on-existing-road-telegraph-says.html
The U.K. may for the first time
impose a toll on an existing stretch of road, the  Daily
Telegraph  reported, citing Transport Secretary Justine Greening.  A toll is being considered for a widened, 20-mile section
of the A14 highway in Cambridgeshire, England, the newspaper
cited Greening as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
